After I updated to 0.90, the game crashes a lot. What am I doing wrong?

BTW I use a mac.

Well, there's not a lot we can deduce from that amount of information...

I've moved this to the forum's Support section, so please take a look at the Stock Support thread stickied here. We do need some solid info to be able to give you any real insight, at the very least we'll need your Player.log file and a detailed list of your computer's specs.

Ok, I use a macbook pro 15 (late 2013) 2 GHz and 8 GB ram. ThatÃ‚Â´s pretty much all i know. The game normally crashes every time I recover a vehicle, and often when I open the map. Thanks for replying BTW!

Same here 10.10

MacBook Pro (Retina, Mid 2012)

16GB memory

no mods

Crash when recovering ship!

This makes the game quite unplayable...

I really love this game, played more than 300 hours (according to steam). And this new updates sounded like a lot of fun but as this is unplayable I'm hesitating to downgrade.
Hopefully they release a new update which will fix the problem.

Even if several people are having repeated crashes on the same platform and version, we don't know whether KSP is crashing for the same reason until you provide good information.

As vexx32 said, please read Stock Support & Bug Reporting Guide and provide all of the requested information.

Yes, you will actually need to read the thread. It tells you where to find the information we need to have before we are able to help you. As with a lot of computer issues, without knowing a good deal of information, we can offer only semi-useful solutions at best, and most of those will be useless to you.

There's this: http://bugs.kerbalspaceprogram.com/issues/3869

I've had repeated crashes since 0.90.0 went live, so I've parked the game until that bug is closed.

  • KSP version Steam OS X version 0.90.0
  • A detailed explanation After a very short time playing, CTD or Beachball Of Doom requiring force quit. I didn't notice a specific set of circumstances that caused the lock up or crash - most often it was entering or exiting a "building", but not always.
  • A .craft file or save file: new game started after 0.90.0 released, I don't think a save file is relevant here though.
  • The ouput_log.txt or player.log https://drive.google.com/file/d/0ByAbHM_2x8TbMTBBUGdPdlJCdXM/view?usp=sharing player.log
  • OS X Yosemite 10.10.1 (14B25)
    MacBook Pro (Retina, 15-inch, Late 2013)
    2.3 GHz Intel Core i7
    16 GB 1600 MHz DDR3
    NVIDIA GeForce GT 750M 2048 MB (and Intel Iris Pro 1536 MB)
